<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Investigation: FTP Compromise — March 24, 2026</title>
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@300;400;600;800&family=IBM+Plex+Mono:wght@400;500&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
    <style>
        :root {
            --bg: #ffffff;
            --text-main: #1a1a1a;
            --text-muted: #666666;
            --accent: #0055ff; /* Cobalt Blue */
            --border: #e0e0e0;
            --surface: #f9f9f9;
            --code-bg: #f4f4f4;
            --max-width: 1100px;
        }

        * { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }

        body {
            background-color: var(--bg);
            color: var(--text-main);
            font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
            line-height: 1.6;
            padding: 0;
        }

        /* --- Layout --- */
        header {
            border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
            padding: 4rem 2rem;
            max-width: var(--max-width);
            margin: 0 auto;
        }

        .container {
            max-width: var(--max-width);
            margin: 0 auto;
            display: grid;
            grid-template-columns: 250px 1fr;
            gap: 4rem;
            padding: 4rem 2rem;
        }

        @media (max-width: 850px) {
            .container { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 2rem; }
            aside { position: static; }
        }

        /* --- Typography --- */
        h1 { font-weight: 800; font-size: 3.5rem; letter-spacing: -0.04em; line-height: 1; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
        h2 { font-weight: 600; font-size: 1.5rem; letter-spacing: -0.02em; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); padding-bottom: 0.5rem; }
        .metadata { font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace; font-size: 0.8rem; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--text-muted); margin-bottom: 2rem; }
        
        /* --- Sidebar Navigation --- */
        aside { position: sticky; top: 2rem; height: fit-content; }
        .nav-list { list-style: none; }
        .nav-item { margin-bottom: 1rem; }
        .nav-link { 
            text-decoration: none; 
            color: var(--text-muted); 
            font-size: 0.9rem; 
            font-weight: 500;
            transition: color 0.2s;
        }
        .nav-link:hover { color: var(--accent); }
        .nav-link.active { color: var(--text-main); border-left: 2px solid var(--accent); padding-left: 1rem; }

        /* --- Content Blocks --- */
        section { margin-bottom: 6rem; scroll-margin-top: 2rem; }
        p { margin-bottom: 1.5rem; font-size: 1.1rem; color: #333; }
        
        .artifact-box {
            background: var(--surface);
            border: 1px solid var(--border);
            padding: 2rem;
            margin: 2rem 0;
            position: relative;
        }

        .artifact-label {
            font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace;
            font-size: 0.7rem;
            color: var(--text-muted);
            position: absolute;
            top: -10px;
            left: 20px;
            background: white;
            padding: 0 5px;
        }

        .code-block {
            font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace;
            background: var(--code-bg);
            padding: 1.5rem;
            border-radius: 4px;
            font-size: 0.9rem;
            overflow-x: auto;
            margin: 1rem 0;
        }

        /* --- Interactive Elements --- */
        .question-card {
            border-left: 4px solid var(--border);
            padding-left: 1.5rem;
            margin: 2.5rem 0;
        }

        .question-text { font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; display: block; }
        
        .answer-reveal {
            background: none;
            border: 1px solid var(--accent);
            color: var(--accent);
            padding: 0.5rem 1rem;
            font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
            font-weight: 600;
            cursor: pointer;
            transition: all 0.2s;
            margin-top: 0.5rem;
        }

        .answer-reveal:hover { background: var(--accent); color: white; }

        .answer-content {
            display: none;
            margin-top: 1rem;
            padding: 1rem;
            background: #f0f4ff;
            border-radius: 4px;
        }

        .answer-content.show { display: block; }

        footer {
            border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
            padding: 4rem 2rem;
            text-align: center;
            font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono', monospace;
            font-size: 0.8rem;
            color: var(--text-muted);
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

    <header>
        <div class="metadata">Lab Investigation // Case: 2026-03-24-FTP</div>
        <h1>Investigating FTP Compromise</h1>
        <p style="max-width: 600px; color: var(--text-muted);">A forensic analysis of unauthorized access, staged data, and exfiltration artifacts within a customer environment.</p>
    </header>

    <div class="container">
        <aside>
            <ul class="nav-list">
                <li class="nav-item"><a href="#objectives" class="nav-link">01. Objectives</a></li>
                <li class="nav-item"><a href="#compromise" class="nav-link">02. Compromised Users</a></li>
                <li class="nav-item"><a href="#staging" class="nav-link">03. Staging & Downloads</a></li>
                <li class="nav-item"><a href="#telemetry" class="nav-link">04. Application Telemetry</a></li>
                <li class="nav-item"><a href="#infrastructure" class="nav-link">05. Actor Infrastructure</a></li>
                <li class="nav-item"><a href="#review" class="nav-link">06. Customer Review</a></li>
            </ul>
        </aside>

        <main>
            <section id="objectives">
                <h2>Student Learning Objectives</h2>
                <ul style="margin-left: 1.5rem;">
                    <li>Identify anomalies within Wireshark capture using knowledge of common misconfigurations. [cite: 38]</li>
                    <li>Identify potentially compromised FTP users and data exfiltration destinations. [cite: 39, 40]</li>
                    <li>Review forensic endpoint artifacts including XML configuration files. [cite: 41]</li>
                    <li>Develop pertinent questions for customer environment discovery. [cite: 42]</li>
                </ul>
            </section>

            <section id="compromise">
                <h2>Identifying Compromised Users</h2>
                <div class="question-card">
                    <span class="question-text">What FTP users appear to be compromised?</span>
                    <button class="answer-reveal" onclick="toggleAnswer(this)">Reveal Findings</button>
                    <div class="answer-content">
                        Maintenance_Jill and Anonymous. [cite: 45, 46]
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="artifact-box">
                    <span class="artifact-label">Network Parameters</span>
                    <div class="code-block">
                        Source IP: 192.168.2.196 [cite: 48]<br>
                        FTP Server: 192.168.2.122 [cite: 50]<br>
                        Client IP: 192.168.2.196 [cite: 52]
                    </div>
                </div>
            </section>

            <section id="staging">
                <h2>Staged and Stolen Data</h2>
                <p>During the investigation, specific commands and network patterns were used to confirm unauthorized data movement.</p>
                
                <div class="question-card">
                    <span class="question-text">How was the data download confirmed?</span>
                    <button class="answer-reveal" onclick="toggleAnswer(this)">Reveal Technical Detail</button>
                    <div class="answer-content">
                        Through the <strong>RETR</strong> command and referencing <strong>PASV</strong> port numbers to identify the TCP 3-way handshake and FTP-Data transmission. [cite: 57, 58]
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="artifact-box">
                    <span class="artifact-label">Staging Directory</span>
                    <p style="font-family: 'IBM Plex Mono'; font-size: 0.9rem;">C:\Users\test\Desktop\FTP\Lending [cite: 60]</p>
                </div>
            </section>

            <section id="telemetry">
                <h2>Application Specific Telemetry</h2>
                <p>The following artifacts from the victim endpoint overlap with the network investigation:</p>
                <ul style="margin-left: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 2rem;">
                    <li><strong>Site Manager IPs:</strong> Identifying known remote hosts. [cite: 68]</li>
                    <li><strong>Filezilla.xml:</strong> Confirming local file paths. [cite: 69]</li>
                    <li><strong>Recent Servers:</strong> Log of destinations used for exfiltration. [cite: 70]</li>
                </ul>
            </section>

            <section id="infrastructure">
                <h2>Threat Actor Infrastructure</h2>
                <p>Authorization was granted for a restricted "Hack Back" to identify infrastructure specifics.</p>
                
                <div class="artifact-box">
                    <span class="artifact-label">Exfiltration Artifacts</span>
                    <p><strong>Base64 Hash:</strong> <code>V2hvTkxDaXNUaGlzIT8y</code> [cite: 76]</p>
                    <p><strong>Resolved Username:</strong> <code>threatactor</code> [cite: 78]</p>
                    <p><strong>Storage Path:</strong> <code>/home/threatactor</code> [cite: 80]</p>
                </div>
            </section>

            <section id="review">
                <h2>Client Environment Review</h2>
                <div class="question-card">
                    <span class="question-text">Is Maintenance_Jill authorized for this activity?</span>
                    <p>No. Maintenance_Jill's authorized device is located at <strong>192.168.2.250</strong>, but logins were seen from <strong>192.168.2.196</strong>. [cite: 85]</p>
                </div>
                <div class="question-card">
                    <span class="question-text">Who should have access to the FTP server?</span>
                    <p>Internal policy states only <strong>Finance personnel</strong> should have access. [cite: 87]</p>
                </div>
            </section>
        </main>
    </div>

    <footer>
        &copy; 2026 — Forensic Investigation Training // Prepared for March 24th Session
    </footer>

    <script>
        function toggleAnswer(btn) {
            const content = btn.nextElementSibling;
            content.classList.toggle('show');
            btn.textContent = content.classList.contains('show') ? 'Hide Findings' : 'Reveal Findings';
        }

        // Simple scroll spy for navigation
        window.addEventListener('scroll', () => {
            const sections = document.querySelectorAll('section');
            const navLinks = document.querySelectorAll('.nav-link');
            
            let current = '';
            sections.forEach(section => {
                const sectionTop = section.offsetTop;
                if (pageYOffset >= sectionTop - 60) {
                    current = section.getAttribute('id');
                }
            });

            navLinks.forEach(link => {
                link.classList.remove('active');
                if (link.getAttribute('href').includes(current)) {
                    link.classList.add('active');
                }
            });
        });
    </script>
</body>
</html>
